parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag did not deploy in a crash
airbag warning light on the dashboard
injury or death due to lack of airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts to repair the Takata airbag recall can lead to a prolonged period of risk for drivers and passengers.

but parts are not available for repair
inability to use front passenger seat
feeling of unsafe driving conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window master switch can lead to a fire hazard.
symptoms: Power window master switch malfunction
smoke or fire from the switch
inability to use power windows.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to speed out of control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without pressing the gas pedal
and may not respond to braking; the vehicle may speed up to high speeds
making it difficult to control; the vehicle may not slow down or stop even when the brake pedal is pressed; the accelerator pedal may stick or feel spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal does not respond or feels spongy; the vehicle does not slow down or stop even when the brake pedal is pressed; the vehicle may accelerate unexpectedly; the airbags may deploy unnecessarily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Erratic accelerator pedal response can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels sticky or spongy; the vehicle accelerates or decelerates unexpectedly; the vehicle may hesitate or lag when accelerating; the vehicle may suddenly speed up or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays incorrect or inconsistent readings
the vehicle stalls or runs out of fuel
the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause smoke or fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Smoke or fire around the front driver-side door window
the circuit board is smoking
the windows can cause smoke and fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflators can cause injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The front passenger airbag inflator may fail to deploy
the driver's airbag is damaged and may fail to deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The key fails to turn from the "on" position to the "start" mode

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of mechanical components can cause loss of power, accidents, or injuries.
